In general, the custodial parent can get child support from the other parent, the non-custodial parent. The custodial parent is the parent who has physical custody of the child. This means that the child lives with this parent most of the time. If the two parents were never married to each other, there be an Acknowledgment of paternity or order of affiliation to establish paternity.The custodial parent can get child support even if that parent can support the child on their own. Kemasan pakai dus tebal, cocok juga untuk kado atau hadiah
